text: Please remove the state and assignee and running time from the area just below the title in the header of Execute sidebar. KEEP them in the area below the HR/border, and add the status color/icon, and the running time, to the lower area.

proposedTasks.title: Deduplicate Execute sidebar header and consolidate status details below divider
proposedTasks.description: In the Execute phase task detail sidebar, the task state, assignee, and running time currently appear in the header area just below the title AND in the detail section below the horizontal rule. Remove state, assignee, and running time from the header area (below the title, above the HR). In the lower detail area (below the HR), keep all three fields and enhance them: add the status color indicator and icon next to the status value, and display the running time with its existing formatting. The title itself remains in the header. Acceptance criteria: (1) Header area shows only the task title  no state badge, assignee, or running time. (2) Below the HR/border, status is displayed with its corresponding color and icon. (3) Below the HR/border, assignee and running time are displayed. (4) No information is lost  all three fields remain visible in the lower section. (5) Layout is visually consistent with the existing sidebar design language.

taskTitles: Deduplicate Execute sidebar header and consolidate status details below divider
